The impact of forensic analysis on investigations is significant, with 36.2% of respondents
responding that forensic analysis "sometimes" has an impact, 21.5% stating that it "often,"
20.8% believing that it "always," and 17.7% stating that it "rarely" does. This underlines the
vital role that digital forensics plays in modern investigations, where digital evidence can often
be key to solving a case. The persistent influence of forensic analysis highlights the need of
